<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-356-678  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 356 678.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  May 24 1989 n107 p99(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business and Computer Publications1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A flexible friend. (Software Review) (Budget Express, add-in forLotus 1-2-3) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Jenkins, Rhys.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Budget Express, Symantec's Lotus 1-2-3 add-on for budget creation,consolidation and handling, is a well-thought-out package thatshould be seriously considered by anyone who has the need tocreate budgets.andP;  For the average user, Budget Express' mainattraction is its ability to handle hierarchies, such as rent andheating under the general category of buildings.andP;  Perhaps BudgetExpress' strongest feature is its ability to consolidate manybudgets into one, creating overall budgets.andP;  The79-pounds-sterling program assumes virtually no knowledge of 1-2-3on the part of the user.andP;  Installation is very easy and the manualis good.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Symantec UK Ltd. (products).andO;Product:   Lotus 1-2-3 (Spreadsheet software) (computer programs)The Budget Express (Spreadsheet software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationAdd-In-On SoftwareSpreadsheets.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   User verdict. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The installation of Budget Express was accomplished with an ease which shouldbe noted by afl software manufacturers.andP;  The manual is good, covering how toget a working copy onto either a floppy or hard disk and also taking you stepby step through installing it into 1-2-3 itself.andM;The manual is divided into two sections, a tutorial and command summary.andP;  Thetutorial is as comprehensive as it is easy to follow and is very &quot;hands-on&quot;.andO;It explains things fully and simply and assumes your knowledge of 1-2-3 isvirtually nonexistent.andP;  It does help, however, if you have some knowledge ofspreadsheets.andM;Users who need more time to familiarize themselves with Budget Express canalso go through the command summary which gives extensive examples for eachcommand using the sample files provided.andM;Budget Express, main appeal to the average user is its ability to handlehierarchies.andP;  For example under a heading of Buildings, there might be theindividual items of Rent, Heating or Insurance, which you may need to take asa single item.andP;  By the simple expedient of indenting the subsidiary itemsfrom the Buildings item, Budget Express will treat them as items under thatheader.andP;  It even helps with the indenting by giving an option to indent anumber of items by a certain amount.andM;Once the individual items have been given headings, Budget Express can thenbe used to produce sub-totals and totals by selecting the header for a listof items.andP;  For example, in the above instance, you would select Buildings,then the Totals option and lo-and-behold a Buildings Total line appears atthe bottom of Rent, Rates, etc.andP;  Items under a header can also be hidden,leaving just the headers.andP;  Hidden items are, in fact, moved either to anotherpart of the spreadsheet or to a disk file.andP;  Once items have been hidden todisk they may be locked, allowing you to pass round the general figures of abudget while maintaining confidentiality of details, such as individualsalaries.andM;Perhaps the strongest feature of Budget Express, however, is its ability toconsolidate a number of budgets into one.andP;  This is done by creating aConsolidation Spec which is in turn used to create the budget.andP;  So, if youhave several buildings each producing its own budget you can, having createdthe Consolidation Spec, easily create an overall budget.andO;</TEXT></DOC>